#Weather API

#Changing the Data Path

The API needs to know where your .zarr model data is stored. You can change this path by editing the config.yaml file located in the root directory.

1. Open config.yaml.
2. Update the outputs_dir under the paths section to point to your new data drive:
    paths:
      outputs_dir: "/new/path/to/your/data_drive"
      run_folder: "fcn3_stormcast"



#Running the Code

1. Open your terminal and navigate to the folder api.
2. Ensure your virtual environment is activated using "source venv/bin/activated".
3. Start the server using Uvicorn:
    uvicorn fast_api:app --reload --host 127.0.0.1 --port 8000

#Running the Code

1. chmod +x start_api.sh
2. ./start_api.sh    or  ~/IdeaProjects/api/start_api.sh

